im J. Long-term clinical outcome of the surgically resected intraductal papillary neoplasm of the bile duct. <em>J Hepatol</em> 2012;57(4):787–793.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jhep.2012.05.008">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22634127/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Long-term+clinical+outcome+of+the+surgically+resected+intraductal+papillary+neoplasm+of+the+bile+duct&amp;author=G+Jung&amp;author=KM+Park&amp;author=SS+Lee&amp;author=E+Yu&amp;author=SM+Hong&amp;author=J+Kim&amp;publication_year=2012&amp;journal=J+Hepatol&amp;pages=787-793&amp;doi=10.1016%2Fj.jhep.2012.05.008&amp;pmid=22634127">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">73.</div><div id="r73" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Kang MJ, Jang JY, Lee KB, Han IW, Kim SW. Impact of macroscopic morphology, multifocality, and mucin secretion on survival outcome of intraductal papillary neoplasm of the bile duct. <em>J Gastrointest Surg</em> 2013;17(5):931–938.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11605-013-2151-3">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23371308/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Impact+of+macroscopic+morphology%2C+multifocality%2C+and+mucin+secretion+on+survival+outcome+of+intraductal+papillary+neoplasm+of+the+bile+duct&amp;author=MJ+Kang&amp;author=JY+Jang&amp;author=KB+Lee&amp;author=IW+Han&amp;author=SW+Kim&amp;publication_year=2013&amp;journal=J+Gastrointest+Surg&amp;pages=931-938&amp;doi=10.1007%2Fs11605-013-2151-3&amp;pmid=23371308">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="li